10/04/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Ivica Racan will meet with the trade union representatives to discuss amendments to the labour act, according to a government press release issued Wednesday (9 April).
Negotiations will continue in the trilateral council, representing employers, trade unions and state institutions.
At issue are regulations concerning termination of employment contracts and severance pay.
(Infoinvest, HINA - 09/04/03)
